critique: This document is an executive order that allows the Senate Committee on the Judiciary to inspect income, estate, or gift tax returns for the years 1960 to 1964. The purpose is to study the applicability of antitrust and monopoly laws to professional boxing. There is no direct indication of ideological tilt, immigration approach, expansion of executive power, federalism implications, national security concerns, economic regulation, or social inclusion. Therefore, most axes should be scored as neutral.
